        <headline>Flash Flood Watch issued July 31 at 9:58AM MDT until August 1 at 12:00AM MDT by NWS Great Falls MT</headline>
        <description>* WHAT...Flash flooding and debris flows caused by excessive
rainfall from thunderstorms are possible over the Horse Gulch burn
scar.

* WHERE...A portion of central Montana, including the following
areas, Big Belt, Bridger and Castle Mountains and Canyon Ferry
Area.

* WHEN...From 3 PM MDT this afternoon through this evening.

* IMPACTS...Moderate to heavy rainfall over the Horse Gulch burn
scar is possible. Heavy rainfall could trigger flash flooding and
debris flows in and near the recent wildfire burn scar.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...
- National Weather Service Meteorologists are forecasting heavy
rainfall from thunderstorms over the Horse Gulch burn scar,
which may lead to flash flooding and debris flows.
- http://www.weather.gov/safety/flood
</description>
        <instruction>You should monitor later forecasts and be prepared to take action
should Flash Flood Warnings be issued.</instruction>
